==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gavotte
<hw>Gav"otte</hw></mhw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gavotte</ets>, fr. <ets>Gavots</ets>, a
people inhabiting a mountainous district in France, called
<ets>Gap</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A kind of difficult, old
formal French dance in quadruple time.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Music composed in quadruple time for dancing the
gavotte, having a dance tune which has two brisk and lively, yet
dignified, strains in common time, each played twice over.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gawby</ent>⟦br⟧
